The useEffect hook in React lets you perform side effects in functional components, 
such as fetching data, manipulating the DOM, or setting up event listeners.
It is the functional component equivalent of lifecycle methods like componentDidMount,
componentDidUpdate, and componentWillUnmount used in class components. 

useEffect is a react hook used to handle side effect in function components.
------------------------------------------------
useeffect(() =>{
    //side effect code
return() => {
     //cleanup code 
};
}, [dependencies]);
-----------------------------------------------------
common side effects
api calls
setinterval/settiime out
dom update
event listeners
local storage
subscriptions  

